    <h2>What is this?</h2>
    <p>
      When you use a custom font (like a font from Google Fonts),
      <a href="https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2016/02/font-display#differences_in_font_rendering_today">most
        modern browsers</a>
      wonâ€™t render the text immediately. Instead, they will keep the text
      hidden until the font is downloaded â€“ or until 3 seconds pass. If a user
      opens a page with such font from a slow connection (e.g. from mobile),
      it will look like this:
    </p>
    <p>
      <video autoplay muted>
        <source src="/loading-video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        <source src="/loading-video.webm" type="video/webm" />
